<dl id="n09070f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09070f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09070f"> 70(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dwarf W stands / on chair <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09070f"><li>FW 198.24 </li><li><a href="../../flex/h/lexh.htm#n09070f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/h/l39h.htm#n09070f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n09070f">MS BL 47474-107</ms> </li><li>JJA 48:040 <a name="hd2" href="../../FF/fdra/hda.htm#hd2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/h/hd2.htm#n09070f">Draft: I.8&sect;1.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">En 1883, Louise Bichat mourait aux Sables-d&apos;Olonne et les journaux d&apos;alors rapportent qu&apos;elle &eacute;tait mari&eacute;e au sieur Callias depuis trois ans, sa taille ne d&eacute;passait pas o m. 8o. &ldquo;C&apos;&eacute;tait une femme avec un temp&eacute;rament de fer &hellip;. Elle avait avec son mari de fr&eacute;quentes disputes. On dit m&ecirc;me que pour avoir raison de ce dernier, quand tous les deux &eacute;taient ivres, <mark>elle montait sur une chaise</mark>, et croyez bien que ce n&apos;&eacute;tait pas le mari qui avait le dessus. <br><font color="green">[In 1883 Louise Bichat died in Sables-d&apos;Olonne and the newspapers reported that she had been married to a Mr Callias for three years and that her height never exceeded 0.80 metres [2 foot 7]</font>. &ldquo;She was a woman with an iron temperament &hellip;. She frequently quarelled with her husband. It is even said that, to get the better of the latter, when both of them were drunk, she would stand on a chair and you can believe that it was not the husband who had the upper hand.&hellip;&rdquo;] <small> Caufeynon, <a name="CAUF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CAUF"><cite title="source">Les Monstres Humains</cite></a> (Paris, 1900) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
